message.content:
Neural Networks, Reinforcement Learning. 

Neural Networks: The paper compares the performance of a PI controller with two neural networks - one trained to predict the steady-state output of the PI controller and the other trained to minimize the n-step ahead error between the coil output and the set point. 

Reinforcement Learning: The paper also includes a reinforcement learning agent trained to minimize the sum of the squared error over time. The agent is compared with the PI controller and the two neural networks.
